games.summary: CHARLOTTE, N.C. Moussa Diabate had a career-high 18 rebounds and 12 points for the Hornets and Miles Bridges flirted with a triple-double before finishing with 10 points, nine rebounds and nine assists.
blurbs: 📋 Moussa Diabate (CHA) made just his 3rd start this season. 12 pts, 18 reb.

games.summary: Michael Porter Jr . scored 28 points, Egor Demin added 20 and the Brooklyn Nets beat the Philadelphia 76ers 114-106 on Tuesday night.
blurbs: 🆕 Jared McCain (PHI) made his first start of the season. 39 min, 10 pts.

games.summary: Josh Giddey had 19 points, 15 assists and 11 rebounds, Coby White hit a tiebreaking free throw with 1.9 seconds left, and the Chicago Bulls rallied for their fourth straight victory, 126-123 over the Atlanta Hawks on Tuesday night. White finished with 24 points for the Bulls, who trailed by 18 points in the second quarter, by 15 late in the third and by 10 with less than six minutes left.
blurbs: ⬆️ Asa Newell (ATL) played 21 min (season avg: 10). 13 pts, 7 reb, 0 ast.

games.summary: Donovan Mitchell scored 27 points, Sam Merrill added 22 and the Cleveland Cavaliers pulled away in the second half for a 141-118 victory over the New Orleans Pelicans on Tuesday night. Nine of the 11 players used by the Cavaliers players scored in double figures as they won consecutive games for the first time since Nov.
blurbs: ⬆️ Thomas Bryant (CLE) played 22 min (season avg: 9). 15 pts, 7 reb, 1 ast.
⬆️ Bryce McGowens (NO) played 31 min (season avg: 17). 8 pts, 7 reb, 3 ast.

games.summary: scored 24 points, Ryan Rollins had 23 and the Milwaukee Bucks , playing their seventh consecutive game without the injured Giannis Antetokounmpo , beat the Indiana Pacers 111-94 on Tuesday night. Kyle Kuzma scored 15 and Bobby Portis had 14 points and a team-high nine rebounds as the Bucks shot 51% to snap a three-game losing streak.
blurbs: 📋 Ethan Thompson (IND) made just his 5th start this season. 3 pts, 5 reb.
📋 Bobby Portis (MIL) made just his 4th start this season. 14 pts, 9 reb.

games.summary: Scottie Barnes scored 27 points and grabbed eight rebounds, and the Toronto Raptors beat the reeling Miami Heat 112-91 on Tuesday night in the final pre-Christmas game for both teams. Immanuel Quickley scored 18 for the Raptors — who got their 18th win in their 31st game of the season.
blurbs: 📋 Sandro Mamukelashvili (TOR) made just his 5th start this season. 14 pts, 6 reb.

games.summary: Cooper Flagg had 33 points, nine rebounds and nine assists, and Anthony Davis had 31 points and nine rebounds as the Dallas Mavericks beat the Denver Nuggets 131-130 on Tuesday night. Flagg, who has four double-doubles but no triple-doubles, tied his career high for points in a quarter with 14 in the first – hitting all seven field-goal attempts, two from downtown.
blurbs: ⬆️ Ryan Nembhard (DAL) played 33 min (season avg: 21). 11 pts, 3 reb, 7 ast.
🆕 Jaden Hardy (DAL) made his first start of the season. 28 min, 10 pts.
⬆️ Caleb Martin (DAL) played 25 min (season avg: 9). 9 pts, 4 reb, 3 ast.

games.summary: Anthony Edwards scored 38 points to help the Minnesota Timberwolves beat former teammate Karl-Anthony Towns for the first time and hold off the New York Knicks 115-104 on Tuesday night. Towns scored a season-high 40 points before fouling out in the final minute for the Knicks (20-9) in the absence of fellow All-Star Jalen Brunson , who rested his previously injured ankle.
blurbs: ⬆️ Mike Conley (MIN) played 30 min (season avg: 19). 8 pts, 1 reb, 2 ast.
⬆️ Bones Hyland (MIN) played 25 min (season avg: 13). 9 pts, 3 reb, 4 ast.
🆕 Tyler Kolek (NY) made his first start of the season. 31 min, 20 pts.

games.summary: Keldon Johnson had 25 points, Stephon Castle added 24 and the San Antonio Spurs stormed past Oklahoma City 130-110 on Tuesday night, winning their seventh straight game and beating the Thunder for the second time in 11 days.

Dillon Brooks scored 25 points, Devin Booker added 21 and the Phoenix Suns pulled away in the second half to beat the Los Angeles Lakers 132-108 on Tuesday night. Reaves finished with 17 points on 6-of-11 shooting off the bench, while LeBron James led the Lakers with 23.
blurbs: 🆕 Nick Smith Jr. (LAL) made his first start of the season. 28 min, 12 pts.

games.summary: Santi Aldama made seven 3-pointers and scored a career-high 37 points to lead the Memphis Grizzlies to a 137-128 victory over the Utah Jazz on Tuesday night. Cam Spencer dished out a career high 13 assists to go with 11 points, while Aldama added a season-high seven assists to help the Grizzlies snap a two-game losing streak.
blurbs: 🆕 Kevin Love (UTAH) made his first start of the season. 29 min, 6 pts.
⬆️ Kyle Filipowski (UTAH) played 35 min (season avg: 23). 25 pts, 13 reb, 4 ast.
⬆️ Taylor Hendricks (UTAH) played 27 min (season avg: 15). 21 pts, 4 reb, 1 ast.
🆕 GG Jackson (MEM) made his first start of the season. 30 min, 18 pts.
📋 Cam Spencer (MEM) made just his 4th start this season. 11 pts, 3 reb.

games.summary: PORTLAND, Ore. -- — Desmond Bane scored 23 points, Anthony Black added 22 and the Orlando Magic turned away Portland's comeback attempt Tuesday night for a 110-106 victory over the Trail Blazers.
blurbs: ⬆️ Caleb Love (POR) played 34 min (season avg: 17). 17 pts, 3 reb, 1 ast.
📋 Tyus Jones (ORL) made just his 5th start this season. 16 pts, 4 reb.
⬆️ Noah Penda (ORL) played 24 min (season avg: 11). 8 pts, 6 reb, 2 ast.

games.summary: SACRAMENTO, Calif. Tobias Harris scored 24 points for the Pistons, who have won nine of 11.

Kawhi Leonard scored 41 points and James Harden added 29 as the Los Angeles Clippers beat the Houston Rockets 128-108 on Tuesday night. The Clippers, who trailed by six points after one period, outscored Houston 34-23 in the second and led 63-58 at the break.
blurbs: 🆕 Brook Lopez (LAC) made his first start of the season. 27 min, 5 pts.
